description: Spotted on a the wall of a planter, while the sprinkler system was running. Using scale, the snail is approximately 3.3 cm in length (from tail to head). Scale bar in third photo added using ImageJ, using 2.41 cm as the diameter of a U.S. quarter.

I've never seen these before.  Three individuals about one foot apart resting under a plastic pool tubing
Simply walking down suburban street, as they do.
Sitting on my Meyer lemon tree - on a leaf. Brown base shell about one inch to a point with lighter brown stripes about ever quarter inch.
Possible funnel web spider? Or sheet web?
I believe this is a lacewing egg. It is on a stalk, raised above the leaf.
Saw two house finches. This is just one.
Not sure what bird this is. Seems almost the size of a mourning dove. Sings a lot.
Pretty sure it is an Allen's Hummingbird, but hard to be sure with the light I had.
